FBIS3-11804 "drlat059_c_94023" FBIS-LAT-94-059 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Mar 1994 MEXICO Financial Leaders Urge Investors To Remain Calm PA2503190294 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 1600 GMT 25 Mar 94 PA2503190294 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [From the "Panorama Newscast"] [Excerpts] [passage omitted] The Mexican financial sector has asked investors to remain calm and to trust the country's economic plan. Interviewed separately, Manuel Robleda, Antonio del Valle, and Roberto Hernandez have agreed Mexico's economic program is more viable now than ever. Robleda, president of the Mexican Stock Market, has explained Mexican negotiable documents for sale on international markets over the past two days have received reactions which although not favorable were not negative; thus, he said, investors should maintain their usual calm. Meanwhile, Antonio del Valle, director of the (?Premio International Group), has said this is not the time to speculate, but rather to work for the economy's success. Roberto Hernandez, president of the Mexican Association of Banks, has urged everyone to remain calm, because Mexico's economic stability is real; thus, he said, investments should be made in pesos. [passage omitted] Interviewed after the second confirmation of the economic pact, Hernandez, who is also a National Bank of Mexico board member, said Mexico's induction into the OECD clearly proves Mexico is considered a first world country.
